    {
      "change": "Retained presentation mode -> ability to answer inferential questions as directional",
      "reason": "The study compares performance across presentation conditions and reports that students performed significantly better in picture-only and print-with-picture than print-only, consistent with an experimental condition affecting outcome."
    },
    {
      "change": "Retained presentation mode moderates reading skill level-ability to answer inferential questions",
      "reason": "The effect of reading skill level on inferential-question performance differed by mode: skilled readers outperformed less skilled readers only in the print-only condition, with no group differences in the picture conditions."
    },
    {
      "change": "Added reciprocal moderation: reading skill level moderates presentation mode-ability to answer inferential questions",
      "reason": "The abstract describes an interaction pattern between presentation mode and reading skill level on inferential-question performance; per the moderation rule for interaction effects, both reciprocal moderation entries should be included."
